Execute only PHASE 10.2.

Goal:
Implement entitlement checks, usage metering, and quota enforcement.

Create/update:
backend/app/billing/entitlement_service.py
backend/app/billing/usage_meter.py
backend/app/billing/quota_service.py

Update:
backend/app/core/events.py
backend/app/core/config.py
backend/app/auth/rbac.py
backend/app/auth/dependencies.py
backend/app/api/backtesting.py
backend/app/api/scheduler.py
backend/app/api/content.py
backend/app/api/marketplace.py if present
backend/app/api/realtime.py if present

Tests:
backend/app/tests/test_entitlements.py
backend/app/tests/test_usage_meter.py
backend/app/tests/test_quota_service.py
backend/app/tests/test_phase10_tenant_isolation.py

Config:
USAGE_METERING_ENABLED=true
USAGE_ENFORCEMENT_ENABLED=true
USAGE_RESET_MODE=monthly

Entitlement service methods:
- get_plan_for_org(organization_id) -> BillingPlan
- check_feature(organization_id, feature) -> EntitlementDecision
- check_quota(organization_id, workspace_id, metric, increment=1) -> EntitlementDecision
- require_feature(feature)
- require_quota(metric, increment=1)

Rules:
- Enterprise plan allows custom limits.
- Free plan must be safe and limited.
- If billing disabled in dev, allow but mark mock/dev mode.
- If billing provider fails and BILLING_FAIL_CLOSED=true, block paid-only features.
- Never bypass tenant isolation.
- Entitlement checks must be used by:
  - backtest run
  - optimization run
  - scheduler job creation
  - content creation
  - marketplace plugin install
  - realtime stream access
  - enterprise export

Usage metrics:
- api_requests
- backtests_run
- optimizations_run
- content_items_created
- content_posts_attempted
- scheduler_jobs_created
- scheduler_jobs_run
- iot_actions_requested
- marketplace_plugins_installed
- worker_tasks_enqueued
- realtime_connections
- storage_mb_estimated

Usage meter methods:
- record_usage(organization_id, workspace_id, metric, quantity=1, source=None, resource_id=None, metadata=None)
- get_usage_summary(organization_id, workspace_id=None)
- get_metric_summary(organization_id, workspace_id, metric)
- reset_period_if_needed()

Rules:
- Usage records tenant-scoped.
- Do not record secret payloads.
- Usage metering failure must not crash core system.
- Quota checks must fail safely if enforcement is enabled.

Quota service methods:
- can_consume(organization_id, workspace_id, metric, quantity=1) -> EntitlementDecision
- consume(organization_id, workspace_id, metric, quantity=1, source=None, resource_id=None) -> EntitlementDecision
- get_quota_status(organization_id, workspace_id=None) -> dict

Rules:
- Quota checks happen before expensive operations.
- If quota exceeded, return standard API error code: QUOTA_EXCEEDED.
- Quota events must be logged.
- Emit:
  usage.recorded
  usage.quota.warning
  usage.quota.exceeded
- Warning threshold at >80%.

Validation:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

